PRIVACY POLICY FOR GYMSUITE

Last Updated: December 30, 2025

1. INTRODUCTION
GymSuite ("we," "our," or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your information when you use our gym management application.

2. INFORMATION WE COLLECT
   a) Personal Information:
      - Name, email address, phone number
      - Date of birth and gender
      - Emergency contact information
      - Payment and billing information
      
   b) Gym Activity Data:
      - Membership details and subscription status
      - Attendance records and check-in/check-out times
      - Workout preferences and fitness goals
      - Progress tracking and performance metrics
      
   c) Technical Information:
      - Device information and operating system
      - IP address and location data (if permitted)
      - App usage analytics and crash reports

3. HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION
   - Manage your gym membership and account
   - Process payments and billing
   - Track attendance and facility usage
   - Provide customer support and notifications
   - Improve our services and app functionality
   - Ensure security and prevent fraud
   - Send important updates about your membership

4. INFORMATION SHARING
   We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share information only:
   - With your explicit consent
   - To comply with legal requirements
   - With trusted service providers who assist our operations
   - In case of business transfers or mergers

5. DATA SECURITY
   We implement industry-standard security measures including:
   - Encrypted data transmission and storage
   - Secure authentication systems
   - Regular security audits and updates
   - Access controls and staff training
   - Secure cloud storage with backup systems

6. DATA RETENTION
   - Active membership data: Retained while membership is active
   - Inactive accounts: Data deleted after 2 years of inactivity
   - Payment records: Retained for 7 years for legal compliance
   - You may request data deletion at any time

7. YOUR RIGHTS
   You have the right to:
   - Access your personal information
   - Update or correct your data
   - Request deletion of your account
   - Opt-out of promotional communications
   - Receive a copy of your data
   - Lodge complaints with data protection authorities

8. COOKIES AND TRACKING
   Our app may use cookies and similar technologies to:
   - Remember your preferences
   - Analyze app performance
   - Provide personalized experiences
   - You can manage cookie preferences in your device settings

9. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES
   We may integrate with third-party services such as:
   - Payment processors (for secure transactions)
   - Analytics services (for app improvement)
   - Cloud storage providers (for data backup)
   - These services have their own privacy policies

10. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
    Our services are not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we discover such information, we will delete it immediately.

11. INTERNATIONAL TRANSFERS
    Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own. We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your data during such transfers.

12. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes through the app or via email. Your continued use constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

13. CONTACT US
    If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us:
    
    Email: privacy@gymsuite.com
    Address: [Your Gym Address]
    Phone: [Your Contact Number]
    
    Data Protection Officer: [If applicable]

14. LEGAL BASIS (FOR EU USERS)
    We process your data based on:
    - Contract performance (membership services)
    - Legitimate interests (service improvement)
    - Legal obligations (record keeping)
    - Your consent (marketing communications)

15. DISPUTE RESOLUTION
    Any disputes regarding this Privacy Policy will be resolved through:
    - Direct communication with our support team
    - Local data protection authorities
    - Applicable legal jurisdiction in your region

By using GymSuite, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to this Privacy Policy.

